The script performs a multinomial logistic regression to predict Latent Class Analysis (LCA) membership, using 'Stagnant Neutral' as the reference category. 1. Data Preparation: It loads the processed dataset and filters for respondents who have an assigned LCA_Class. Missing values in the predictors (Positive_Affect, Negative_Affect, HIDDG, QDB, QKB_1_4, QKB_1_11) are imputed (using median for continuous/ordinal and mode/constant for categorical) to preserve the sample size. 2. Feature Engineering: HIDDG (job profile) and QDB (sector) are dummy-encoded. An interaction term between QKB_1_4 (Regular Training) and QKB_1_11 (Employee Involvement) is created. 3. Multicollinearity Check: Variance Inflation Factors (VIF) are calculated for all predictors to ensure multicollinearity does not destabilize the model. The diagnostics are printed and saved to data/vif_diagnostics.csv. 4. Model Fitting: The statsmodels MNLogit function is used to fit the model. The BFGS optimization method is prioritized as it is more robust to near-singular matrices and perfect separation. 5. Results Extraction: The full coefficient table (including standard errors, z-statistics, p-values, and odds ratios) is printed for each non-reference class and saved to data/mnlogit_results.csv. 6. Policy-Lift Probabilities: The model predicts class membership probabilities for four specific combinations of the organizational enablers (Low/Low, High/Low, Low/High, High/High, corresponding to values 1 and 5 on the Likert scale), while holding all other variables at their means. The helper function get_series_or_nan safely extracts model attributes as pandas Series to prevent scalar-related errors.

