Addressed the ConvergenceWarning by switching the primary fitting method to fit_regularized(alpha=0.1, L1_wt=0.0). The L1_wt=0.0 specifies Ridge regression (L2 penalty), which shrinks coefficients towards zero and prevents them from blowing up to infinity when perfect separation occurs. Simplified the fallback logic to just use the regularized fit directly, as standard MLE is failing.

